</style></head><body style=" font-family:'Cantarell'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;">
<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Spiritual maturity is priority one. Devotion to teaching means growing in spiritual maturity.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Spiritual maturity requires sitting under biblical teaching.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Following Jesus requires a radical shift in our world-view. Switching from a pagan/secular world-view to a biblical world-view.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">A world view is what dictates how you live your life and encourage others to live theirs.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">A biblical world view is a set of values, beliefs, and morals that we live by and dedicate ourselves to.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">The first commandment from God is that we are to have no other gods before Him. Pagan world views popularly replace ourselves with God where we try to define our own life-purpose and moral values.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Look to Jeremiah 17 when told to &quot;follow your heart&quot;.</li></ul>
<p style="-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:1; text-indent:0px;"><br /></p>
<p style="-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;"><br /></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">The second part of this fabric is joining in the fellowship. You cannot have a church without a fellowship of people participating in it and loving/teaching/supporting each other.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">The fellowship replaces and gives purpose and voice to those who are in the faith. We show others the success of Jesus when we are together and cooperating in the church.</li></ul></body></html>